I moved to Seattle after college to start my career and I miss owning a dog, but I'm not quite ready to commit to a full time dog-relationship: so here I am in doglimbo. I am a young professional, working for Microsoft, so I have the option to work from home and I would love to dog walk/watch during the day, or sit overnight. I am a very healthy eater, active runner and yogi, active hiker, and Pacific Northwest native. Please feel free to reach out with any questions!  I am currently unable to host dogs due to a new request from my landlord, but I am more than happy to stay at your home or drop in!  P.S. I am also happy to take dogs on runs outisde with me if their joints are happy and healthy.  I look forward to meeting you and your pooch,  Hayley"
